<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9faf04c-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s617m"><num value="617m">§ 617m.</num><heading> Reclamation law applicable</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This subchapter shall be deemed a supplement to the reclamation law, which said reclamation law shall govern the construction, operation, and management of the works herein authorized, except as otherwise therein provided.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9faf04d-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1928-12-21/ch42/s14">Dec. 21, 1928, ch. 42, § 14</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/45/1065">45 Stat. 1065</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9faf04e-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9faf04f-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idc9faf050-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The reclamation law, referred to in text, is defined in <ref href="/us/usc/t43/s617k">section 617k of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
